Effective cloud monitoring involves collecting metrics, logs, alerts, and health information continuously.

Recommended practices include:

* Configure alerts for critical resources
* Monitor application performance
* Review security events
* Analyze usage trends
* Perform proactive maintenance

For example, administrators receive alerts when CPU utilization exceeds predefined thresholds.

A real-life use case is preventing outages before users notice service degradation.

Cloud monitoring supports operational excellence and continuous improvement.
